So we chose this place bc it had great reviews and unfortunately this shop seems to be experiencing quite a bit of disorganization and difficulty getting on top of what seems to be a greater workload than they can handle at the moment.  We brought the car in need of a new engine and agreed upon price ($3000), for a used engine with under 50k miles and a completion date which came and went with no call from them.

My husband initiated contact to be told the engine had come in that day( was a Friday) and that Monday it would be put in.  They expected to have it ready the next Friday. So that next Friday came and went and I initiated contact and got Rod who said, "we finally got the right engine in and so hopefully should be done by next. Thursday or Friday.

So the jury is out.. Fingers crossed

< text>
Finding an honest auto mechanic can be challenging. Please read my story. I have been a customer of Phil‚Äôs Auto Clonic for over 20 years.

I have a 2005 Honda Pilot. It has been a great car to own. It has 180,000 miles so I worry about car problems.

My wife and I were in Sacramento when I discovered I had to have some brake work. At a Sacramento National brand tire shop I was told I needed to replace my lower control arm bushing. The mechanic showed me that it was obviously worn and needed replacing. This bushing is made of heave duty rubber and I could see it looked worn. I told the mechanic I would get it fixed when I got home.

I took my Car to Phil‚Äôs Auto Clinic where I have been going for over 20 years fully expecting to replace the control arm bushing. The manager at Phil‚Äôs said ‚Äúlet‚Äôs see if the bushing is bad before we replace it. Sure it looks weathered on the outside but if it‚Äôs bad you will have abnormal tire wear and you should be feeling it in the steering.‚Äù  He put my car on the lift and checked for play in the joint. There was none. My tires have around 30,000 miles an them and they are wearing evenly with no abnormal wear. The manager said ‚ÄúWe do not recommend replacing the bushing at this time because it is not worn out‚Äù.  I was very thankful.

6 months later I was at the local Honda dealer for a factory recall. While I was there they told me I needed to replace my lower control arm bushing. The service writer said ‚Äú You can see for yourself it look worn out‚Äù. I said I would check with my mechanic. I went back to Phil‚Äôs again and said the Honda dealer says I should replace that control arm bushing.  The manager said we could replace it but ‚ÄúWe are not recommending replacement because it is functioning perfectly. It is not worn out‚Äù!

I realized then and there that Phil‚Äôs Auto Clinic is possibly the only auto repair shop that cares about honesty and integrity whether they make a profit or not!  I appreciate that!

5< /Rating>
<Review>My 2005 Honda Accord Hybrid has 200k miles on it.  Its hybrid battery has been out of commission for the last 40k miles (the check engine light and IMA lights have been engaged this entire time) but has operated fine.  Well, this year when renewing my registration I was told I needed a SMOG check for the first time.  Got the car SMOG'd only to find out a check engine light = automatic fail.  I went to the Honda dealership and asked if they could disengage the light or something, considering the code triggering the light (P1600) had NOTHING to do with emissions.  They said my options were A. Pay $3500 to get a replacement battery or B. trade the car in.

NICE SCAM YOU'VE GOT GOING THERE HONDA.  Especially rich because at the time of the purchase, the dealer said after the battery dies the car can be operated as a gas-powered car.  Using this BS loophole in California's SMOG check, Honda coerced me into replacing the battery (which costs about the same as the value of the car).

Anyway I found Phil's on Ebay after looking for a less expensive option.  The battery included new cells (Honda uses refurbished), was $1300 cheaper, and comes with a 2 year warranty.  I was not intending to replace the battery but being forced to, Phil's auto clinic was a good choice.  Took about 3 hours, and he was able to SMOG the car after installing the battery.

I would like to note that my mileage has not increased as much as I had anticipated.  On gas I got about ~19 in the city and ~34 on the freeway.  Now I get ~24/38.  Still, this is around the EPA MPGs.

Overall I'm satisfied, happy I wasn't forced to junk my car and also glad I didn't have to give the cons at Honda any money.  Will not be buying Honda again.  Would recommend Phil's Auto Clinic for a hybrid battery replacement.</Review>< Pics>
None</Pics>

<Time>1601144428966<//Time><Rate>5</Rate>< text>
Santa Clara city library at the Central Park location has curbside pickup which I found very useful. I was impressed with the traffic management the crew had set up. I arrived on my bicycle and waited in the walk-up line. When it was my turn I showed them my card. I was offered a grab bag option like mystery or young adult. All in all it was a very smooth experience. I recommend watching the video they've posted on the library's website ahead of time just so you know what you're getting into.</text>

< Rate>
5< /Rate>
< username>
Paul Cwick (Shveek)<//username>
<gmapID>0x808fb57edaed9903:0x881294cf2f99f6fc<//gmapID>< Text>
Best library in the area, in my opinion.  Clean, quiet, well-lighted, well-staffed, spacious, with plenty of computers and plenty of comfortable places to sit (a godsend on hot Summer days, when one needs a quiet place to cool off.)  The small section with tables, where one may eat a lunch, is also nice (I only wish it had more tables, as they fill up quickly.)  The library is also relatively free from unnecessary distractions (such as noisy crazy people), unlike, say, the Sunnyvale Library.  The "Quiet Nook" is another excellent feature of this library, one which I sincerely wish other libraries would adopt:  A nice, quiet, secluded little room by itself with desks equipped with privacy-hutches, and kept mercifully-quiet, for those times when one needs to work free from noise & distractions.  Other useful resources available at this library as well, such as scanners, copiers, etc.  All in all, an excellent library, one which is my first choice for virtually all my library needs.  The only real criticism I can make is the fact that the parking is really not adequate to the needs of the location.  With the numerous special activities going on at either the library, the Swim Center and Central Park, that parking-lot tends to fill up awfully fast and parking soon becomes unavailable (especially when some spaces are blocked-off by Park staff for some bizarre reason.)  There is some underground parking available underneath the library, but it is small & difficult to maneuver in there and also fills up quickly.  What is really needed is a large, multi-level parking-structure for the Library, the Swim Center and Central Park.  I for one would support the construction of such a structure, as I believe it is needed.< /Text>

<Name>Hannah Mathews</Name>< Text>
A nice quiet studying place that I go to everyday to do my homework and check my email. I reserved one of the study rooms on the 2nd floor to study in and help my siblings with their homework. The next day I tried to reserve a room again for the same reason but I was denied. I asked why and the lady at the desk said my siblings were too young. But I had no warning of this because apparently only 13 year olds and up are allowed. But there is no sign anywhere saying this. And I have seen toddlers and young children repeatedly in there, and they have not been asked to leave. I told the lady this and she responded with a quite rude comment of saying how they are an exception like I was allowed the privilege of using the room. < name>
Sarah Lussier<//name>
<date>1531443685277</date><Rate>4< /Rate>< review>
A very nice public pool! Kids under 7 are free and adults are $6.00. The facilities are updated and the life guard to patron ratio is fabulous! There were so many guards monitoring the two pools. The kiddie pool is a great depth that goes from friendly for learner's to babies (3.0 ft to 3.6 ft back to 3.0- 1.6 ft.) There isn't a lot of shade close to the kiddie pool, but there are umbrellas and the shade from the buildings. A great location to cool off.< /review>

<response>None< /response>< Review>
Boarded my 3 dogs ( 1 senior small dog and 2 large older dogs with bad anxiety) for 12 nights. One of my large dogs had failed the test day at Camp Bow Wow, the other large dog passed but was shaking by the gate the entire time. We decided to try Zuri instead after much research and we are so glad we did. We watched our dogs on the daycare cameras every day- both large dogs did incredible with the other dogs, and the staff were very attentive. More than once we caught staff sitting in the small dog area and petting/playing with dogs. My one large dog with the worst anxiety laid along a wall the entire first day, clearly a little scared. The next day I saw t hat a piece of play equipment had been moved to where she laid the day before where she could hide under the piece of equipment, So they were clearly paying attention to her and felt that would make her more comfortable which was very sweet. All of my dogs upon pickup were not crazy trying to get out like they have been before, they were all calm and we genuinely believe they had an enjoyable stay. We will definitely use them again!< /Review>

<rating>1< /rating>< Text>
I made an appointment for my dog with Zuri, but when we showed up they informed me (and not at the time I made the appointment) that my dog needed to have all his vaccinations updated.
When I went to walk out the door they said, "Oh don't worry about it this time, we will just take him!"
Fearing that there was a reason for my dog needing to be vaccinated, I decided against letting them break their own policy (why have a mandatory vaccination policy, then let people in regardless?), and took my dog to the vet, where we got his vaccinations done. After that, I took him back to Zuri and checked my dog in for his grooming.
5.5 Hours later (how in the world does it take 5 hours to wash a dog?) my dogs eyes and face were swollen shut, an allergic reaction from the vaccinations, but NOBODY at Zuri commented on the fact that this was happening.
While my dog was in their care, I feel like he wasn't taken care of. He was clean yes, but his face was swollen shut and he was running a fever and freaking out, traumatized from the allergic reaction and nobody noticing...
Not a single employee said anything to me about his condition. So very disappointed that the people that work for Zuri didn't care enough to notice what was happening with my dog's health.

We will not be coming back! And we will be letting anybody we talk to know just how little care was actually shown to our animal while under the careless eye of Zuri employees.<//Text>

103323588377608478591</UserId.>
<Resp>None</Resp>< text>
My favorite sushi restaurant in downtown San Francisco. The restaurant is small and cozy. They have a great selection of sushi - vegetarian, cooked and raw sushi.  The prices  are typical of sushi restaurants - specialty rolls are usually 12 and up. They also have a alcohol menu so you can buzzed or drunk as you eat sushi. My favorite is the vegetarian sushi - the deli maki roll which consists of deep fried sweet potato, avocado and cream cheese. It is creamy and sweet. The second favorite is the Lion king.

Treat yourself and dine in because the chef uses brightly colored sauces to decorate the plates/boards. Not only that, the sauces go wonderfully with the sushi.  Because if the care that went into the presentation, it makes you feel like you are eating at a high-class sushi restaurant.<//text>

<review>(Translated by Google) Inside Out Emotional Whirlwind is a Family-friendly Attraction that opened on June 28, 2019 At Pixar Pier in Disney California Adventure, The Attraction uses The Maliboomer Space A Attraction that was Closed in 2010, its Space was unoccupied for a Long Time and Anchor a Pixar Pier Neighborhood known as "Headquarters of Inside Out." It also uses the A Bug's Land Flik's Flyers Attraction Infrastructure that was replaced by it, The Attraction has 5 Soundtracks that represent the 5 Emotions of Riley Andersen from the 2015 Inside Out Movie as Joy (Joy), Sadness (Sadness) ), Fear (Fear) Disgust (Dislike) and Anger (Fury), The Type of this Attraction is from the Balloon Race, It is found in Pixar Pier.

<Rating>2</Rating>< Text>
After receiving my order, I overheard employees bemoaning how sauces/ingredients weren't dated, which didn't inspire much confidence in the franchise and products. The lettuce was browning and didn't taste fresh. The wrap I received, whilst being made by a trainee associate receiving training, was 30-40% smaller than I'm accustomed to. I chose Togo's for my meal due to their (historically) filling portions and fresh ingredients, but this location didn't live up to those expectations. Neither Sun Chips nor Coke Zero were available as well. One star for the wrap still tasting alright despite it's size and brown lettuce, another for the friendly staff.< /Text>

<text>Had a great first time experience using Heaven's Best Carpet Cleaning.  I usually use another company but happened upon their 5-Star yelp reviews and gave them a try.  My experience from start to finish was 5-Stars - I called Monday morning and Alex was at my house the next day at 2:30 sharp.  It took him about an hour to clean my master and living room area rug.

I had a couple of pet urine and vomit stains from a few years that weren't able be cleaned in the past using the steam method - Heaven's Best technique got all the stains out, they don't use steam and therefore doesn't saturate the carpet and it was dry in about an hour - (probably drys faster in the summer when it's hot)

Alex was friendly, professional and fast. They are now my new go to carpet cleaning company moving forward.  I highly recommend them!< /text><pics>None< /pics>< Resp>

<Text>On March 14,  I purchased several pieces of furniture with Angel Gazleh of Ashley's Furniture in Yorba Linda and scheduled it for delivery on April 18, 2020 as I was moving to a new place on that date. All of the furniture that I ordered was delivered on time except for one piece of furniture and this furniture was rescheduled to arrive May 31. I was informed this was due to it being on backorder. However, it did not arrive on that date. I called to get status on this after several days and was told it was sitting in a warehouse after being on hold for several hours. I did not understand why I was not advised of this but nevertheless I scheduled a delivery date with the representative on the phone for a new delivery date of June 6.

I received a call before June 6 and was advised that the item was now on backorder and won't be available until the 16th of June and it was set to be delivered between 8:30 a.m. and 12:30 a.m. After expressing my frustration with this constant rescheduling and hours wasted on hold I was offered a $50 gift card due to the inconvenience and I was promised a return call from the manager. However, I neither received a phone call nor the gift card.

I chose to work from home on the date of the delivery as Ashley's requires that you remain available. The day came and I again received NO DELIVERY. After checking status I saw that the delivery was "unable to be completed" and when I tried to call the driver I received no response only a Voicemail that was in spanish. I tried several times to reach him to no avail. I was then forced to called Ashley's Yorba Linda's store customer service 3 times  (twice the phone call was dropped or no one picked up) and was on hold for SEVERAL HOURS to which I was told that they were having furniture delivery issues due to COVID-19 which could not be accurate as I received prior shipments with no issue. < Review>
The furniture was delivered on the day we scheduled in the store, 8 days after the date of purchase. It was delivered in good condition except that the bottom shelves of the cabinet are missing the support pins so the glass falls if you touch it. A bit upset that the delivery people did not catch that, but then again I work for a super high end office furniture dealership so I have high expectations. I'm going to need to call them now to get some pins <sigh>. For the money we paid the furniture seems reasonably well built. The display cabinet is very solid and heavy and the couches are light. The couch cushions are not uncomfortable but they are brand new so a bit stiff. The floor models obviously get a lot of use so they were softer and broken in a bit more. I think ours will soften up. Our experience in the store was good and the salesman was friendly and helpful and gave us a very good discount.<//Review>

< review>
Let me start by saying that I don't usually post negative reviews because I like to give everyone the benefit of having a bad day or such, but 2 bad encounters with the same person weeks apart must mean something. Anyway, we have shopped at Ashley for many years, but usually at their Colton location. We have since moved from that area and have shopped at this location at Savi twice - both times included rude service from the manager. (I forget her name, but she is the blonde one with tattoos.) How she ever got to be Manager is beyond me! In addition to her rudeness, she couldn't even do simple math on the items we were trying to purchase, and argued with us on the price. Both of our encounters involved using gift cards that we received from the Colton store due to promotions they had on a  large purchase that we made.
The manager treated us as if we were low life's that were trying to get one over on the store. She tried telling us we could not use the gift card for sale items, and was not going to give us change, or a smaller amount gift card for the difference of the purchase. She was going to keep the change! The time before we returned an item and she was not going to allow it because we purchased it with a gift card even though we were fine with being refunded store credit or another gift card. Both times she was wrong, and extremely rude, making silly comments that were completely unwarranted, such as suggesting that we were just going to return the item later for cash. The rest of the staff here are great. It was actually entertaining watching them roll their eyes behind her back, as they must unfortunately have to deal with her incompetence on a daily basis.
We still have some gift card left and will make the longer drive to another location.< /review>
